<subSubSection id="C37565586424FF8CFF1AF01248CFC127" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD036D36424FF8CFF1AF01248CBC024" blockId="20.[189,441,1622,1649]" box="[189,441,1622,1649]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading id="D09881BF6424FF8CFF1AF01248CBC024" bold="true" box="[189,441,1622,1649]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16424FF8CFF1AF01248CBC024" bold="true" box="[189,441,1622,1649]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Preliminary remark</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD036D36424FF8CFF1AF0C148CFC127" blockId="20.[189,1400,1669,1906]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226424FF8CFF1AF0C148E3C0F5" author="Adamczak F. J." box="[189,401,1669,1696]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="271 - 311" refId="ref25784" refString="Adamczak F. J. 2006. Contributions to Palaeozoic Ostracod Classification [POC], N ° 41. &quot; Nonkloedenellacean &quot; ostracods 1. Family Geisinidae Sohn, 1961. Assured podocopines. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Abhandlungen 240: 271 - 311. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / njgpa / 240 / 2006 / 271" type="journal article" year="2006">Adamczak (2006)</bibRefCitation>
revised the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506424FF8CFDDFF0C14B87C0CA" authorityName="Sohn" authorityYear="1961" box="[632,757,1669,1695]" class="Ostracoda" family="Geisinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geisinidae</taxonomicName>
and considered that 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506424FF8CFC49F0C24C05C0CA" authority="Coryell &amp; Rogatz, 1932" authorityName="Coryell &amp; Rogatz" authorityYear="1932" box="[1006,1399,1669,1696]" class="Ostracoda" family="Geisinidae" genus="Knoxina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Platycopina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16424FF8CFC49F0C24D23C0CA" box="[1006,1105,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Knoxina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226424FF8CFBFEF0C14C05C0CA" author="Coryell H. N. &amp; Rogatz H." box="[1113,1399,1669,1696]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="378 - 395" refId="ref27800" refString="Coryell H. N. &amp; Rogatz H. 1932. A study of the ostracode fauna of the Arroyo Formation, Clearfork Group of the Permian in Tom Green County, Texas. American Midland Naturalist 13 (6): 378 - 395. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2419859" type="journal article" year="1932">Coryell &amp; Rogatz, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16424FF8CFF57F0EC4804C097" box="[240,374,1704,1730]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Chesterella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226424FF8CFED8F0EC4BE4C097" author="Croneis C. &amp; Gutke L." box="[383,662,1704,1730]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="33 - 63" refId="ref28136" refString="Croneis C. &amp; Gutke L. 1939. New Ostracodes from the Renault formation. Denison University Bulletin, Journal of the Scientific Laboratories 34: 33 - 63." type="journal article" year="1939">Croneis &amp; Gutke, 1939</bibRefCitation>
are synonyms, the latter being junior synonym of the former. Thus, both have typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506424FF8CFE4AF08F4B18C0B0" authorityName="Sohn" authorityYear="1961" box="[493,618,1739,1765]" class="Ostracoda" family="Geisinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geisinidae</taxonomicName>
outline, deep adductorial sulcus, prominent costa along ventral margin and one or two longitudinal costae. He also considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506424FF8CFC1DF0B44D6FC15C" authorityName="Coryell &amp; Rogatz" authorityYear="1932" box="[954,1053,1776,1801]" class="Ostracoda" family="Geisinidae" genus="Knoxina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Platycopina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16424FF8CFC1DF0B44D6FC15C" box="[954,1053,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Knoxina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an “unclear [genus] to be investigated in details” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE4B226424FF8CFE78F1564A69C178" author="Adamczak F. J." box="[479,795,1810,1837]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="271 - 311" refId="ref25784" refString="Adamczak F. J. 2006. Contributions to Palaeozoic Ostracod Classification [POC], N ° 41. &quot; Nonkloedenellacean &quot; ostracods 1. Family Geisinidae Sohn, 1961. Assured podocopines. Neues Jahrbuch fur Geologie und Palaontologie, Abhandlungen 240: 271 - 311. https: // doi. org / 10.1127 / njgpa / 240 / 2006 / 271" type="journal article" year="2006">Adamczak 2006: 294–295</bibRefCitation>
). As this revision is out of the scope of the present contribution and material, we choose to keep the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506424FF8CFCF5F1724AC7C11A" authorityName="Coryell &amp; Rogatz" authorityYear="1932" box="[850,949,1846,1871]" class="Ostracoda" family="Geisinidae" genus="Knoxina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Platycopina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91BEAC16424FF8CFCF5F1724AC7C11A" box="[850,949,1846,1871]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Knoxina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D506424FF8CFC7BF1714D2BC11A" authorityName="Sohn" authorityYear="1961" box="[988,1113,1845,1871]" class="Ostracoda" family="Geisinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Geisinidae</taxonomicName>
until its family position is thoroughly revised.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
